msItem.title: Menahic ul-usûl üd-diniye ila mevakıf il-makasıd ıl-ayniye

supportDesc.extent: iv, 102, ii leaves : 200 x 135 (153 x 170) mm bound to 250 x 143 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Contemporary foliation in ink in Hindu-Arabic numerals (1-9, 11-102), upper left recto; no catchwords.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 19 long lines, ruled with a misṭarah.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh with elements of nastaʻlīq.

decoDesc.decoNote: Headpiece in gold, pink and blue (f. 1v); textblock border-ruled in gold; rubrications in red.
List of other works on this topic

binding.p: Bound in black leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); onlay stamped paper mandorla with pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces; red leather doublure; slip case in red leather with gold-tooled (now green) frame; in the center, the number 142, above and to the right, an orange and white stamp with the number 215.

origin.p: The item is dated Ramaḍān 1119 A.H. (1707) and was copied by a scribe named Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥājj Walī al-Dīn (f. 102v).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis (bookplate inside front cover).
